
The original circuit that kicked off this project. A modified and mutated combination of Tim Escobedo’s Ghost Dance Wah circuit snippet (https://nexp.pt/escobedo.html) and the 4069 State Variable Filter (https://electro-music.com/forum/topic-69887.html), with the addition of a basic LFO and homemade vactrol. The inputs and outputs from the original schematics have been routed incorrectly to create feedback wackiness, potentially contributing to the resulting circuit’s sensitivity to capacitive touch. Seven points along the circuit have been outboarded to brass body contacts, and all potentiometers and switches are without covers to act as touch points as well. 

Tone, timbre, and pitch can be altered by touching the brass buttons, bare potentiometers, and switches. Touching multiple points in different combinations and with varying pressure results in different sounds, including starving out the circuit. One of the switches turns on a vibrato effect, whose speed can be adjusted with one of the pots. Very chaotic and nonlinear; options are expanded when ran through Alto Screecher 2.
